    {
      "title": "Hyperaccurate Pathtracer",
      "mediaType": "video",
      "src": "/assets/img/scripting/pathtracer/showcase.mp4",
      "alt": "Hyperaccurate Pathtracer",
      "descriptionHtml": [
        "This system was made to be a very accurate pathtracer, or what most people would typically call raytracing.",
        "It can calculate everything from: Lighting, Textures, PBR, Reflections, Refractions, Caustics, HDRI (Sky), and more.",
        "This would not exist without PoptartNoah's pathtracer module, which I heavily modified and optimized to make this system possible.",
        "Nearly no original code from PoptartNoah's module exists in this system, however it would be wrong to say that it's a completely original creation."
      ],
      "descriptionMedia": [
        {
          "title": "4K Image",
          "src": "/assets/img/scripting/pathtracer/4k.png"
        },
        {
          "title": "Global Illumination",
          "src": "/assets/img/scripting/pathtracer/globalillumination.png"
        },
        {
          "title": "Mirror Reflections",
          "src": "/assets/img/scripting/pathtracer/mirror.png"
        },
        {
          "title": "Sunrays",
          "src": "/assets/img/scripting/pathtracer/sunrays.png"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "NPC Advanced Sight System",
      "mediaType": "video",
      "src": "/assets/img/video/npcsight.mp4",
      "alt": "NPC Advanced Sight",
      "descriptionHtml": [
        "This sight system is a highly optimized (like, REALLY optimized) sight system for any kind of NPC",
        "I was annoyed that all NPC systems use raycasting just for the torso or the head despite needing accuracy, so I made this system that detects any kind of limb and the location inside of the limb.",
        "Despite raycasts happening 60 times a second (maximum, not frame dependant), this system uses a modified version of <a href=\"https://devforum.roblox.com/t/making-a-combat-game-with-ranged-weapons-fastcast-may-be-the-module-for-you/133474\" class=\"hover-link\">FastCast</a> to handle it's raycasts in a few hacky ways."
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Tool-based Gun system",
      "mediaType": "video",
      "src": "/assets/img/video/gun_system.mp4",
      "alt": "Tool-based Gun system",
      "description": [
        "This was done by me and a friend, where we made an entire tool-based gun system and only in a tool in about 6 hours, all animations, visual effects, sound effects, and about half of the scripting was done by me."
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Truck Driving System",
      "mediaType": "video",
      "src": "/assets/img/video/truck_system.mp4",
      "alt": "Truck Driving System",
      "description": [
        "This entire truck driving system was done by me completely solo.",
        "It took me nearly 3 days and 10 sources just to get the suspension to look realistic and good..."
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Versatile Climbing System",
      "mediaType": "video",
      "src": "/assets/img/video/climbing_system.mp4",
      "alt": "Advanced First Person Movement System",
      "description": [
        "This system is for climbing and has multiple configurations per-ladder and globally for all kinda of climbing, whether ladder, rock-climbing, etc, this system can do it."
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Real Time Global Illumination + Reflections",
      "mediaType": "video",
      "src": "/assets/img/video/global_illumination_and_reflections.mp4",
      "alt": "Global Illumination + Reflections",
      "description": [
        "After creating a raycast system that was so optimized where 1000 raycasts per frame would take up 2.6% of ALL script activity, I added a Bouncecast system to it.",
        "That bouncecast system looked somewhat like light bouncing, so I wanted to push the system to it's limits, and I managed to make a real-time Global Illumination system and reflections after a few days of work.",
        "GL is done with Color inheritence and very tiny lights and lots of raycasts",
        "Reflections are done with Viewport Frames set to angle with the camera and to hold visuals, also using raycasting for shadows and better visuals.",
        "This system runs at a comfortable and stable 120-130 FPS on my RTX 4070."
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Sane Camera and Footstep System",
      "mediaType": "video",
      "src": "/assets/img/video/sane_camera_and_footstep_system.mp4",
      "alt": "Sane Camera and Footstep System"
    },
    {
      "title": "Random Room Generation",
      "mediaType": "video",
      "src": "/assets/img/video/random_room_generator.mp4",
      "alt": "Random Room System"
    },
    {
      "title": "Advanced AI System",
      "mediaType": "video",
      "src": "/assets/img/video/advanced_ai_system.mp4",
      "alt": "Advanced AI System",
      "description": [
        "This AI system was done as I was very tired of making a new AI from the ground up anytime I wanted to make a roaming AI monster for a horror game.",
        "The system contains 1,356 lines of highly optimized code (for reference, before optimization, the system was nearly 2600 lines of code.)",
        "Fun Fact: Any AI that properly uses this system does NOT have collision on anything other than walls, rather it avoids objects at all costs, meaning it won't get stuck, but it also won't attempt to go through walls or objects."
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "First Person Horror Movement",
      "mediaType": "video",
      "src": "/assets/img/video/firstpersonhorrormovement.mp4",
      "alt": "Advanced First Person Movement System",
      "description": [
        "This is an unfinished movement system and camera system for my game, Sane.",
        "ALL of the movement and camera is done fully custom by reverse engineering Unreal Engine's default first person camera and movement is done without any prior help",
        "Movement and camera work also supports Controller and mobile, albeit cursed, it works and is fully playable."
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Roomba AI",
      "mediaType": "video",
